South Africa shifts to Level 4 Lockdown, today, 1 May, to combat the spread of the coronavirus (Covid-19). The draft regulations according to the Disaster Management Act were issued last week and after consultation, the regulations were gazetted and signed by Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs Minister N. Dlamini-Zuma on 29 April. The National Command Council led by Minister Dlamini-Zuma, briefed the nation on the Level 4 permissions and restrictions according to the Risk Adjusted Strategy, on Wednesday, 29 April. Regulations applicable during Alert Level 4